      "span_text": "Many small-molecule compounds have been developed that inhibit HIF-P4Hs competitively with respect to 2-oxoglutarate leading to stabilization of HIF-α in cultured cells and in vivo. 24, 25 One such compound, FG-4497, has been shown to stabilize HIF-1α and HIF-2α, to increase the expression of Epo mRNA and several other hypoxia-regulated mRNAs in cultured cells and in vivo and to elevate serum Epo and blood hematocrit values in mice and rats without apparent toxicity,"
